<br>
I'd get run3 at 51 asap - being able to run away from most mobs will save you xp in the long run.<br>
<br>
If you do nothing but solo &amp; have epic, get them at 51 - epic pet is overpowered vs. mobs you will be fighting.<br>
<br>
If you group 100% of the time, i'd get aas at 65 fer sure. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buppy>Buppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 1:00:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7766.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: On the way to Arch Convoker</span><hr size=1> First off, get out of the 'int is king' mind set. Once you hit 200 int, you can usually do better by adding  mana items. (Mana/int over 200 is only half the value of below 200.) At 52, that 3 int earring is only giving you 15 mana. Summoned earring is better, even without the effect.<br>
<br>
Get all the HP and mana you can get. The 56 rods still add decent mana regen if you remember to use them, and the more hp you have the less the hit will hurt.<br>
<br>
Third, at 57 switch specs to Conjuration. Bolts and Rains are nice, but your DD spells will get much more use (All non-bolt DD past 57 are conj based). That plus the pets/summons will save you alot more mana.<br>
<br>
Fourth, splitting AA and normal xp does at least seem to slow down disproportionately, so I'd stay at 100% either way, picking up AAs when your at the level to get the ones you want. Of course, it's probably psychological, so feel free to experiment. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Buppyy O'Boom</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
