</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buppy>Buppy</A> at: 11/7/02 1:02:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 7:38:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7766.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: On the way to Arch Convoker</span><hr size=1> Gonna touch on this point-by-point.<br>
<br>
Gear-wise, the best things you can buy are an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Earring of the Solstice</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (great stats, Flowing Thought I) and a Horse. Cheapest horse is 8 or 9k depending on CHA. On Brell the Earring averages for about 10k, I imagine its the same on your server.<br>
<br>
Other useful things to get are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Clay Bracelet</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (right-click Eye of Zomm), <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>White Ceramic Band</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (right-click Burst of Flame), old focus items if you don't have them (right-click Reclaim Energy), <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Amulet of the Grey Wastes</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (Worn Enduring Breath) and an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Enshrouded Veil</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (Summoning Efficiency 3). I weild a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sarnak Summoner`s Dagger</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> because it procs Blaze, our level 34 nuke. Rarely melee with it and there are definitely better stat items out there I can buy, but nothing impresses friends more than a mage going melee and proccing like mad. Plus it looks cool :P<br>
<br>
Quested, I'd definitely snag the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Blessed Coldain Prayer Shawl</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (great stats, Flowing Thought III, buff duration focus) if you don't mind dealing with the MAJOR TIMESINK known as tradeskills. Be prepared to spend tens of thousands of plat (at the least), and a few weeks time maxing out your tradeskills for this quest.<br>
<br>
AA wise, most mages will agree, get run3 ASAP, even if you have Jboots. Back before they changed mod rods, regen3 was the way to go. Nowadays I can't say what you should get, so I stuck with regen3 and I'm still liking it (with TPP and regen3 alone, I regen at 12hp/tic standing and on horseback, 15hp/tic sitting). After that it's a good idea to wait til at least 60 before farming the serious AAs.<br>
<br>
5 Second Pets are your Class AA's Quick Summoning 3. Need to be level 59 and spend 6 AA in General, 12 AA in Archetype, and 18 to max out Quick Summoning.<br>
<br>
I recommend either 100% AA, 100% exp, or 50/50. Either way its gonna be slow.<br>
<br>
Lots of hunting spots on these boards, and an entire section dedicated to them. The most popular solo spots for low 50s seem to be Scarlet Desert on Luclin, Jaggedpine Forest on Antonica, and Ocean of Tears between Freeport and Butcherblock. Forget about soloing the planes until your 60s, btw, IF you can solo them in the first place.<br>
<br>
A good reasonable pace is a blue an hour, anything slower and you're wasting your time grouped or solo. At that rate it will take you 250 hours to go from level 50 to level 60. Post 60 I couldn't tell ya. AA is much easier to get at 60 than at 51, simply because you'll be fighting much higher level monsters for exp at 60 than you would at 51 (IE: Shrooms in FG are high 40s and perfect for a level 60 mage. Whereas Seafuries are low 40s at best and while suitable at 51 are mostly green at 60).<br>
<br>
When you get to 57, you may reconsider your choice of Evocation. 57+ all of our major DDs (Shock of Steel, Shock of Fiery Blades, Black Steel, Sun Vortex) are Conjuration. However all of our rains and bolts (as well as anti-summons) are Evocation. Whichever you pick, be happy with it, and don't let anyone tell you you're wrong. I myself am Conjuration, and it suits me just fine.<br>
<br>
